#compdef ssh-tpm-add
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# Foxboron/ssh-tpm-agent cmd/ssh-tpm-add/main.go —
#   usage at lines 24-35 (the const usage block)
#   parse_argv at lines 45-49 (4 flag.StringVar/BoolVar calls)
#   positional handling at lines 59-70 (default-path
#     fallback to id_ecdsa.tpm + id_rsa.tpm)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# ssh-tpm-add is the **add-sealed-key tool** for the
# ssh-tpm-agent (already covered in the corpus).  Sealed TPM
# keys are SSH private keys created INSIDE the Trusted
# Platform Module so they cannot be extracted from the host
# hardware — even root can't copy the .tpm file to another
# machine and reuse it.  Sister tools: R227's ssh-tpm-keygen
# (creates the sealed keys) and ssh-tpm-hostkeys (lists host
# keys via the agent).  Foxboron's ssh-tpm-* family is the
# de-facto TPM-backed SSH key solution for systems with a
# TPM 2.0 chip.
#
# Critical extraction note: ssh-tpm-add uses **Go's standard
# `flag` package** (NOT cobra/argh/cmdr/clap).  Standard flag
# package has 2 idioms relevant to completion:
#   1. Single-dash long-form is canonical (`-ca URL`, `-host
#      HOST`), but `--` style is also accepted (`--ca=URL`,
#      `--host=HOST`).  Completion uses the single-dash form
#      since that's what upstream's usage block shows.
#   2. No automatic --help — `-h` and `-help` print usage via
#      flag.Usage()
#
# Critical extraction note: ssh-tpm-add's default behavior
# when invoked with NO positional FILE and NO --ca is to
# try BOTH `$SSH_DIR/id_ecdsa.tpm` AND `$SSH_DIR/id_rsa.tpm`
# (main.go:61-67).  This mirrors the default behavior of
# ssh-add (which tries id_ed25519, id_ecdsa, id_rsa).
# Completion does NOT enumerate these defaults; it offers
# `*.tpm` glob.
#
# Critical extraction note: source-direct bug observed —
# `-host` flag's help text reads "ssh hot" (typo) at line 46.
# Completion uses the correct "ssh host".

_arguments \
  '-ca=[CA authority URL for cert-based provisioning]:url:_urls' \
  '-host=[remote SSH host (CA-provisioning workflow)]:host:_hosts' \
  '-user=[remote SSH user (CA-provisioning workflow)]:user:_users' \
  '-c[require SSH_ASKPASS confirmation before each use of the key for signing]' \
  '*:TPM key file (default: ~/.ssh/id_ecdsa.tpm AND ~/.ssh/id_rsa.tpm):_files -g "*.tpm"'
